column5: Did some splake with fishin with some good buddies of mine over the hoildays, Decided to try a new lake, you tell me if it was worth it!  They got a litttle more snow then I thought.. should of brought the Tacoma    The easy part of the walk   Watch for those soft spots around creek mouths!   An hour walk through the bush breakin trail   A start   Little guy!   Meager with one    And another    Close up    Myself with a nice splake    Chirs with a 7lber    Beauties    We landed 23 between the four of us only keepin 5 most were between .5 - 1 lb.  Hope you enjoyed..  Chorme Catcher P.S. first time posting a report with pics, Sorry for the slack job
I would definitely say it was worth it Nice fish, congrats.
wow those splake are huge...good job  Nate
well worth it,congrats on some real nice fish
Looked like a trip well worth the trek! Nice fish!

~~~~AAAAAH the Famous Lake X, also known as Lake Whydoyouwanttoknow~~~~yes a lovely walk through the woods, and down the lake. too far for me if I can't see my rod from the car, it's too far~~~great pics bud only wish I could walk that far
Impressive report, those are incredible fish!
very nice  I have been looking at my maps  and still can't find lake X
It seems to be missing on my maps as well Terry.  Some great looking fish, thanks for the report.
~~~~it's on mine, but it's very old. If you look just N.E. of Upper Canada, where it say Rupert Land, it's just under the Pee about 1.2"
Nice Fish guys, its worth the extra work when you get those results!
The various species in Lake X never ceases to amaze me...
the best multispecies lake in the land that lake x  awesome fish-well worth it!
Great Report, and awesome fish!! That lake X is fantastic no matter what time of year it is.
man those r beauts, make a man jealous
Very impressive catch guys !!!!!...beauty pics too !!.  ..and yes it sure looked like it was worth the gas money for sure....cheers
